<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Seminar In Beijing Honors Renowned Chinese Geologist </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 23 (Xinhua) -- A seminar to discuss the
Collected Works of Li Siguang, one of China's first geologists,
which werte published recently, was held in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Li Siguang (1889-1971) established the field of geomechanics, a
new branch of geology, and devoted himself to education and social
activities.
</P>
<P>
Wen Jiabao, an alternate member of the Political Bureau of the
CPC Central Committee, said at the seminar that scientists should
carry forward the good tradition of veteran scientists and
maintain their style of hard work.
</P>
<P>
Wen, who is also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
Committee, said that Li had made a great contribution both to
establishing China's own industrial basis for energy and raw
materials and to earthquake forecasting and the use of geothermal
heat.
</P>
<P>
He quoted late Chairman Mao Zedong, Premier Zhou Enlai, and
Deng Xiaoping in referring to Li as a banner for the country's
scientists, and said, "The newly-issued collection is a record to
Li's achievements, as well as a scientific summary of his
pioneering research."
</P>
<P>
The collection was also described as a collection of rare
documents for geology research, and scientific and technological
development.
</P>
<P>
It has four million characters in eight volumes on Chinese
geology, glacial geology, geomechanics, regional geology, and
earthquakes.
</P>
<P>
The seminar was presided over by Song Ruixiang, minister of
geology and mineral resources, and attended by Li Ruihuan, a
standing member of the Poltical Bureau of the CPC Central
Committee and chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
