<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India, Germany to Intensify Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 23 (Xinhua) -- India and Germany agreed
today that all-out efforts are needed to further strengthen their
relations, particularly in the economic field, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) said.
</P>
<P>
The need was stressed during talks between Indian External
Affairs Minister I.K. Gujral and visiting German Foreign Minister
Klaus Kinkel here today.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel, who is accompanied by a high-level business delegation,
arrived here today for a three-day official visit to India.
</P>
<P>
At the talks, Kinkel said Germany supported India's
participation in the second summit of Asian and European countries
due to be held in London later this year.
</P>
<P>
Kinkel also met with Prime Minister H.D. Deve Gowda today and
they discussed ways of strengthening Indo-German relations in
various fields including technology transfer, PTI said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
