<HEADLINE> EC Approves Humanitarian Aid for Cambodia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission(EC)
announced today it had approved a package of humanitarian aid
worth ECU 1.5 million (about 1.8 million US dollars) for victims
of conflict in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
It said the aid, channelled by the Euroepan Community
Humanitarian Office(ECHO), would enable non-governmental
organisations to carry out a six-month program of actions focusing
on health and de-mining, mainly in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
According to the EC, inhabitants in the north of Cambodia have
been left isolated and deprived of practically all access to
primary health care as a result of long-running conflict in the
country.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said separate ECHO funding for other projects in
Cambodia so far this year amounted to ECU 560,000(about 672,000
US dollars). 
</P>
</TEXT>
