<HEADLINE> SADC Member States Urged To Coop in Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Southern African
Development Community (SADC) today urged its member states to
cooperate with each other by making complementary instead of
competing tourism policies to protect the environment.
</P>
<P>
Mike Fabricius, an official from the Department of
Environmental Affairs of SADC, told a two-day annual meeting of
the Zimbabwe Council for Tourism today that policy coordination
should be a starting point toward achieving this goal.
</P>
<P>
"There is a lot of work to be done in this regard," he said,
noting that because the region was a major tourist destination,
some governments are tempted to unnecessarily escalate tourism
costs in a bid to earn valuable foreign currency. 
