<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe To Expand Crocodile Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Crocodile Farmers
Association of Zimbabwe said here today that it will work with
the government and other agencies to encourage indigenous
people's participation in the fast-growing crocodile industry.
</P>
<P>
Executive manager of the association, Chris Foot, said "the
entry of more players in the industry" would boost exports which
were expected to increase by five percent this year.
</P>
<P>
While he could not give export figures for last year, Foot
said in 1995, Zimbabwe exported 40,000 skins and 64 tons of meat
then worth four million U.S. Dollars.
</P>
<P>
Most of the products were exported to Japan, Singapore, Europe
and the United States. 
