<HEADLINE> Ethiopia,Norway Sign 2.3 Million U.S. Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- A grant agreement was
signed between Ethiopia and Norway under which Norway will
provide 2.3 million U.S. Dollars of grant to Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ethiopian Ministry of Economic Development
and Cooperation, the Ethiopiana government is making efforts to
sustain the present power supply of the Fincha Power Plant by
preventing a rupture of penstock and to study the possibility of
installing a fourth power unit in the station.
</P>
<P>
The grants will be used to remove the excessive forces in the
steel pipe caused by the movements of penstock foundation slab in
the power station area, secure stability of the penstock
foundation for the future and reduce the risk of collapse due to
external water pressure during dewatering of the penstock.
</P>
<P>
The Fincha Power Plant is the power supplier for Addis Ababa,
capital of the country and for most of the country's industries.
</P>
</TEXT>
