<HEADLINE> Ethiopia To Repatiate 10,000 Somali Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High
Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) and the Ethiopian government
have signed an agreement for the repatriation back to their homes
of up to 10,000 Somali refugees living in refugee camps in
eastern Ethiopia.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the UNHCR said today that the signature
of the agrement is the culmination of preparations which have
been underway since the end of 1994 for the repatriation of an
initial 10,000 somali refugees under a pilot project to
designated locations in north-western Somalia.
</P>
<P>
UNHCR officials in Hargesia have been monitoring the situation
in north-western Somalia with a view to promoting the
repatriation of some 275,000 Somali refugees currently residing
in eight camps in eastern Ethiopia, the release said. 
</P>
