<HEADLINE> Angola Has 3,889 Lepers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- There are now 3,889 lepers all
over Angola, an Angolan health official said here today.
</P>
<P>
Canceigao Palma, who is in charge of the National
Leprosy Control Administration of Angola, told reporters that
1,351 of them are serious patients.
</P>
<P>
She added that most of these lepers are in the provinces of
Uige and Malange in northern Angola, the province
of Benguela in central Angola, and the province of Luanda,
where the capital is located.
</P>
<P>
She said her administration will take measures to control the
spread of the disease this year.
</P>
<P>
On the International Leprosy Day, which falls on January 26,
Angolans will hold commemorative ceremonies in and around the
capital to call for people's attention to the disease. enditem

