<HEADLINE> Jordanian King Arrives in Saudi Arabia for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian King Hussein
arrived in the Saudi city of Madina today on a visit to the
kingdom to hold talks with King Fahd Bin Abdul Aziz and to pay
pilgrimage, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait News Agency (KUNA) quoted Hussein as saying upon his
arrival that his visit aimed to boost cooperation in security and
open the Saudi market for Jordanian goods, as well as allow job
opportunities for the Jordanian citizens in Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian monarch is expected to brief Fahd on the latest
development in the Middle East peace process and the Hebron deal
which allows the Palestinians to control 80 percent of the West
Bank town.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinian National Authority reached the
Hebron deal on January 15, following a few months of hard
negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi cabinet in its session last Monday voiced welcome to
the deal and considered it a step towards achieving a lasting
peace in the region.
</P>
<P>
KUNA quoted Jordanian sources as saying that the two kings will
also discuss ways of fostering bilateral relations, especially in
the economic and trade fields.
</P>
<P>
Jordan's ties with its largest southern neighbor and other
Gulf Arab states were strained when Hussein refused to join the
Arab states and Western countries in condemning Iraqi for its
August 1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Saudi oil supplies to Jordan were cut off then and Amman was
forced to rely solely on Iraq for its energy needs.
</P>
<P>
Things began to improve when Hussein turned against Iraqi
President Saddam Hussein after the defection of two senior Iraqi
officers to Jordan in 1994 and relations between the two countries
improved dramatically after Hussein's last visit to Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
Hussein first visited Saudi Arabia in February, 1994, the first
of its kind since the Gulf War in 1991, but he was not met by Fahd
then. Hussein visited the Saudi coastal city of Jeddah last
August and held his first meeting with King Fahd.
</P>
</TEXT>
