<HEADLINE> 30 Victims of Iftar Poisoning Treated in Egypt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Some thirty construction workers
were hospitalized for food poisoning today after taking their Iftar,
the fast-breaking meal on Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Egypt's MENA news agency quoted a security source as saying
that the Arab Construction Contractors Company treated its workers
with food bought from a restaurant in the Sixth of October City,
about 50 kilometers northwest of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
After the meal of meat, rice and potatoes, most of the workers
suffered acute stomach-ache and violent vomiting. They were later
rushed to hospital.
</P>
<P>
The victims are now in a better condition and police are
looking for the owner of the restaurant, said the source.
</P>
<P>
During the Islamic fasting month of Ramadan which fell on
January 10 this year, Muslims fast from dawn to dusk. Then they
will have Iftar and Sohoor, a square meal at mid-night. 
</P>
