<HEADLINE> Political Party Subsidization Law Adopted in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan parliament today
adopted the Political Party Subsidization Law, with 91 votes
for, one against and 8 abstentions.
</P>
<P>
This law was adopted by the parliament after three days of
discussions.
</P>
<P>
The law stipulates that the parties in the parliament can
obtain subsidies from the state budget and the total subsidies
account for five percent of the budget.
</P>
<P>
And, the subsidies will be distributed to the parties
according to the votes they won in the general elections.
</P>
<P>
The parliament consists of 220 memebers from 12 parties. Of
them, 129 are from the ruling Angolan People's Liberation
Movement and 70 from the opposition National Union for the
Total Independence of Angola. enditem


