<HEADLINE> Zairean Rebels Urged to Move Out of Occupied </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi today called on the rebels in eastern Zaire to move out of
Goma, Bukavu and Uvira to avoid a looming war, according to a
Kenya News Agency report.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan leader pointed out that when the rebels move out of
these cities, it will enable international community to seek
solutions to the crisis in the Great Lakes region without further
bloodshed.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a public rally in Kitui district, Moi noted
that he is opposed to any external forces entering Zaire, which
would result in further aggravation of the crisis.
</P>
<P>
He disclosed that there will soon be a meeting of the regional
foreign ministers to discuss the problems in eastern Zaire and
the Great Lakes region.
</P>
<P>
The sovereignty and territorial integrity of Zaire should be
respected, the Kenyan leader reiterated. 
</P>
</TEXT>
