<HEADLINE> Greek Mother Kills Pregnant Daughter Out of Disgrace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- A 47-year-old Greek mother of
five was charged with murder today after she confessed to
poisoning her pregnant unwed daughter because she could not bear
the disgrace of an illegitimate child in her family.
</P>
<P>
Panayiota Tsifrika, from a small village in the Prefecture of
Elias, Peloponnesos, was remanded in custody Wednesday after an
autopsy on her daughter Constantina, 21, revealed pesticide in her
stomach.
</P>
<P>
Police said Tsifrika confessed to placing a large amount of
pesticide in her daughter's food Sunday night. Constantina was
found dead in her bed Monday.
</P>
<P>
Tsifrika, a widow and mother to another four children, told
police that she wanted "to wipe the stain of disgrace" from her
family and to avert her other children suffering from the "blight"
of an illegitimate child in the family. 
</P>
</TEXT>
