<HEADLINE> Germany to Assist Angola in Mines Removal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The German government will
provide Angola with 1.4 million U.S. Dollars for landmines
removal in the country this year.
</P>
<P>
The decision was announced here today by Hoch Schild, an
official responsible for landmines removal in the German Foreign
Ministry.
</P>
<P>
He said that he hopes the Angolan government will make efforts
to prevent from planting new landmines, adding that it is
senseless to remove landmines while there exists a threat of
laying new mines.
</P>
<P>
According to the UN statistics, there are more than 13 million
landmines in the southern African country with a population of 11
million.
</P>
<P>
Schild arrived here today to start a seven-day working visit
to Angola. During his visit, he will hold talks on landmines
removal with Angolan leaders and UN officials. 
</P>
