<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales Rise in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The value of Hong Kong's
total retail sales in November 1996, estimated at 18.4 billion HK
dollars (2.36 billion U.S. dollars), rose eight percent over the
same month of 1995.
</P>
<P>
After discounting the effect of price changes over the period,
total retail sales went up by three percent in volume, according to
official statistics released today.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the same month of 1995, the increase in November
1996 was mainly attributable to growth in spending on consumer
durable goods, which jumped 12 percent in both value and volume.
</P>
<P>
Concurrently, sales of some other commodities also recorded
increases of various magnitudes in both value and volume terms,
which included jewelry, watches and clocks and valuable gifts;
miscellaneous consumer goods; food; alcoholic drinks and tobacco.
Sales in supermarkets also soared by 11 percent in value and five
percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the period from January to November 1996 with the
same period in 1995, total retail sales rose by six percent in
value and one percent in volume.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
