<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A new flight between Macao and
Zhengzhou, capital of central China's Henan Province, will be
started as of tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of the Henan Provincial Government announced
here today that three flights will be launched between Macao and
Zhengzhou City before the Chinese lunar new year, observed on
February 7.
</P>
<P>
The first plane will land in Macao airport at 3:50 p.m. this
Saturday, followed by the flights on January 28 and February 4.
</P>
<P>
