<HEADLINE> Cambodian People's Party Opens General Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The conference is being held against the backdrop of a new
political alliance, the United National Front, between the CPP's
coalition government partner and rival Funcinpec and other parties
including the opposition Khmer Nation Party.
</P>
<P>
Funcinpec's chairman, First Prime Minister Prince Norodam
Ranariddh, offered to include the CPP in the new alliance, but CPP
Vice President Hun Sen, who is also second prime minister, said
during a break of the opening session that his party would not
join.
</P>
<P>
At the opening session, CPP Chairman Chea Sim, who is also
president of the National Assembly, set out the main tasks of the
congress.
</P>
<P>
He said the party should consider and assess the current
situation and the CPP's political objectives and tasks; define the
CPP's political program on national rehabilitation and
development; amend the statutes of the party; elect additional
members of the Central Committee to meet the requirement of the
party.
</P>
<P>
More than 700 delegates from CPP branches across the country
and abroad attended the congress, which went into closed-door
sessions after the opening session. 
