<HEADLINE> Chinese Environmental Protection Head Meets With US Congressmen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Director of the State Bureau of
Environmental Protection of China Xie Zhenhua today held talks
with a delegation from the US' House of Representatives, headed by
Curt Weldon, chairman of the Committee on National Security
Research and Development.
</P>
<P>
During the 90-minute meeting, the two sides discussed global
environmental protection and environmental cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
