<HEADLINE> Ugandan Railway Workers Strike Ends </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda Railway Workers in
Tororo bordering Kenya ended their three-day strike yesterday
after the striking workers signed an agreement on salary arrears
payment with the Railways Corporation, the local daily ''New
Vision'' reported today.
</P>
<P>
The railway workers went for duty soon after signing the
agreement. Their colleagues at Jinja Station, 100 Kilometers west
of Tororo, also ended their strike yesterday.
</P>
<P>
Four hundred railway workers in Tororo laid down their tools
on January 20, protesting delayed salaries for October, November
and December 1996 and demanding salary increases.
</P>
<P>
The strike disrupted border areas traffic. Cargo wagons were
piled up at a Kenyan border post of Malaba and a Ugandan railway
yard in Tororo. 
</P>
