<HEADLINE> UNITA Censured of Delaying Inauguration of New </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAUNDA,January 24 (Xinhau) --The Angolan government today
censured former rebel UNITA (the national union for the total
independence of Angola ) of delaying the inauguration of the new
Angolan government.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration of the new Angolan government has been
scheduled for January 25, but it will be delayed as some key
issues concerning the formation of the new government have not
yet been settled by the two former rival groups.
</P>
<P>
The inauguration of the new government has to be delayed
because UNITA hasn't decided who will be appointed as
parliamentarians in the new government, government spokesman
Higino Carneiro said in a statement today.
</P>
<P>
He said that the new government's inauguration date can only
be decided after all the elected UNITA parliamentary members
arrive in the capital of Launda.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the post of the UNITA leader Jonas Savimbi in
the new government, Carneiro said that Angolan government
and the UNITA are continuing discussions about the issue. 
</P>
