<HEADLINE> Visitor Arrivals in HK Hit Record in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's visitor arrivals
in 1996 hit a record to reach 11.7 million, according to the Hong
Kong Tourist Association.
</P>
<P>
A latest report issued by the association said that visitor
arrivals last year rose 14.7 percent over the preceding year.
</P>
<P>
The report noted that the year of 1997 marks Hong Kong's return
 to China, which will attract more tourists to the territory from
all over the world.
</P>
<P>
The report estimated that visitors arrivals this year will rise
 six or eight percent over those in 1996.
</P>
<P>
According to the report, Japan was the largest tourist market
last year. Tourist arrivals from Japan were 2.38 million, up 40.9
percent over 1995.
</P>
<P>
The report said that tourist arrivals from the Chinese mainland
were about 2.3 million, accounting for 19.7 percent of the total
visitor arrivals in the territory.  
</P>
</TEXT>
