<HEADLINE> HK Toy Fair Receives Bumper Orders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The 23rd Hong Kong Toys and
Games Fair ended last week with orders totaling 4.2 billion HK
dollars (542 Million US dollars), a rise of 35 percent over 1996,
a spokesman of the Hong Kong Trade Development Council (TDC) said
here today.
</P>
<P>
More than 969 exhibitors from 24 countries and regions were
present at the exhibition, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
He said that business results, with on-the-spot orders worth
1.56 billion HK dollars and another 2.64 billion HK dollars under
negotiation, also set new records, up 45 percent and 30 percent
respectively on the 1996 event.
</P>
<P>
C.S. Lee, TDC's assistant executive director, said that the
Hong Kong Toys and Games Fair is now firmly established as the
Asia-Pacific region's largest and major event for the
international toy industry.
</P>
<P>
He said that the record attendance by overseas buyers and
strong orders at the fair has strengthened Hong Kong's status as
Asia's toy-fair titan.
</P>
<P>
According to the TDC, The 24th Hong Kong Toys and Games Fair is
scheduled for January 7 to 10 in 1998.  
</P>
