<HEADLINE> Macao to Strengthen Cooperation With Zhuhai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Macao and neighboring Zhuhai city
 in China's Guangdong province plan to strengthen cooperation in
investment, cargo transport, finance and Zhuhai's planned bonded
zone, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Huang Longyun, mayor of Zhuhai, said here Thursday at the end
of a three-day official visit to Macao at the invitation of Macao
Governor Vasco Rocha Vieira that both sides have a strong hope for
 closer cooperation.
</P>
<P>
"Zhuhai and Macao have long cherished close relations. During
the current visit, we have had a general arrangement in wide-range
 cooperation between the two sides in order to benefit each
other," he said.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, the mayor had talks with a number of
high-ranking officials of the Macao government, including the
governor himself. He also visited many civil facilities and the
University of Macao.
</P>
<P>
"We have reached a consensus that we both have our own
advantages that could be of help to the other side," said Huang,
adding that "we both have bright prospects."
</P>
<P>
The two sides have discussed the possibility of cooperation in
some 20 projects in investment, cargo transport, finance and
tourism. They also exchanged views on cooperation in such fields
as technology, the planned bonded zone in Zhuhai, as well as in
education and sports.
</P>
<P>
The mayor said that the two sides have agreed to hold further
talks on cooperation. Meetings between specialized teams from
Zhuhai and Macao will be held soon for details of cooperation.
</P>
<P>
With a total population of 500,000, Zhuhai shares a common
land border with Macao. The two sides are closely linked both
geographically and economically.  
</P>
</TEXT>
