<HEADLINE> Leadership in 19 Nigerian Universities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The federal government of
Nigeria has ordered the reconstitution of the leadership of 19
out of the 21 universities in the country.
</P>
<P>
Nigerian Minister of Education mohammed Liman said in a
statement that the governing councils of the remaining two
universities, the University of Nigeria and the Ahmadu Bello
University will be reshaped later.
</P>
<P>
It is belived that the reorganization is connected with the
prolonged strikes by university teachers and students nationwide
in 1996 which led to the actual paralysis of the country's higher
education sector.
</P>
<P>
The teachers demanded higher salaries and better funding for
universities, while the students were angered by the increasing
tuition fees.
</P>
<P>
The government's newly-released budget for 1997 allocated
16.84 billion Naira (about 201 million U.S. Dollars ) for the
education sector, 1.5 billion Naira more than that of 1996.
</P>
