<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Granny Huang and Her Ten Adopted Children </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Life as a successful
restaurateur hasn't diverted Huang Shuqing's attention from needy
orphans.
</P>
<P>
Over the past nine years, the 66-year-old benefactress has
adopted ten kids, and added 12 restaurants to her company's chain.
</P>
<P>
In 1987, Huang, chairman of the board of Shuangshengyuan Food
Company in northeast China's port city of Dalian, met Qu Yanying,
a young girl suffering from meningitis, who was a patient in the
Children's Hospital.
</P>
<P>
When Huang discovered the girl's mother, who is mute, could not
afford the huge medical bills, Huang paid them. And when the girl
recovered, Huang received permission to adopt her.
</P>
<P>
She also adopted Zhao Xiuli, 14, who was unable to finish
primary school education following the death of her parents. Then
came Dang Jie, 9, who was in an orphanage and had recently had
surgery for a cleft palate, a deformity of the lower jaw.
</P>
<P>
Huang's sympathy for children in unfortunate circumstances
stems from her own childhood: her father died when she was young,
and she and her mother were forced to beg in the streets of their
hometown, and later in Dalian.
</P>
<P>
"I will provide the children with good education and let them
contribute to the country with their skills when they grow up,"
Huang said.
</P>
<P>
Qu Yanying, Huang's first adopted daughter, is now a healthy
young woman with a job. "I should thank Mother Huang for
everything I've got," she said.
</P>
<P>
Three of Huang's adopted children are studying in primary
schools, and the rest are in kindergarten.
</P>
<P>
Each holiday season, Huang arranges a family get-together for
her entire clan, including her own four children, her adopted
children and some grandsons and granddaughters.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, she supports six childless widows and widowers. And
she has donated more than 700,000 yuan (84,000 US dollars) to
schools and old folks' homes in the past few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
