<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Sector Thrives in East China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The number of private businesses
has passed the million mark in east China's Anhui province, making
them an emerging force in the provincial economy.
</P>
<P>
There are over one million private businesses with less than
eight employees each, employing a work force of 2.35 million and
possessing a total registered capital of 5.85 billion yuan,
rising 12.1 percent, 15.6 percent and 24.3 percent over 1995
respectively, according to statistics from the provincial industry
and commerce bureau. desk
</P>
<P>
And Anhui had 16,374 bigger private businesses employing
219,000 people, and having 5.03 billion yuan in registered
capital. The three figures grew by 30.6 percent, 20.4 percent and
55.9 percent over the previous year respectively.  
</P>
</TEXT>
