<HEADLINE> King Hussein Returns from Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, January 24 (Xinhua) -- King Hussein of Jordan
returned home early this morning after performing the Umra
(the lesser pilgrimage) in Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, King Hussein met with Saudi King Fahd and
other senior Saudi officials on means of boosting bilateral ties,
Radio Jordan reported.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, King Hussein reiterated the brotherly
relations between Saudi Arabia and Jordan and the strong
historical ties between the two royal families.
</P>
<P>
He also stressed the need to activate the joint efforts and
facilitate the continuation of dialogue for the benefits of the
two countries' causes.
</P>
<P>
Hussein was accompanied by some royal family members and Prime
Minister Abdul Karim Kabariti during his visit.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the Saudi Al Bilad newspaper on
Wednesday, Hussein described Jordanian-Saudi relations as strong
and historic, praising the efforts exerted by King Fahd in
supporting Arab and Islamic causes.
</P>
<P>
Hussein met Fahd last August, which was the first time since
the 1990-1991 Gulf crisis. 
</P>
</TEXT>
