<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Irian Jaya, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.7 on
the Richter scale shocked the eastern town of Wamena and nearby
areas, in Indonesian Irian Jaya province early this morning.
</P>
<P>
The source of the tremor was at 80 kilometer northwest of
Wamena at 3.5 south latitude and 138.2 east longitude, Antara news
agency quoted Putu Pudja, head of the local office of Meteorology
and Geophysics as saying.
</P>
<P>
The quake occurred at 4:06 a.m. today.
</P>
<P>
More than one hour later, that was 5:36 in the morning, a quake
measuring 5.1 on the Richter scale shocked the region again, said
the report.
</P>
<P>
The second quake jolted an area, 120 kilometer northeast of
Wamena at 3.3 south latitude and 139.6 east longitude, Putu said.
</P>
<P>
No immediate reports on casualties and materiel losses were
received yet, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
