<HEADLINE> All Chinese Called to Unite for Reunification (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Meanwhile, new progress has also been made over the past year
in across-Straits economic cooperation and non-governmental
exchanges which still maintain a good momentum of development.
</P>
<P>
The meeting pointed out that the Chinese government will resume
the exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong on July 1 this year and
the implementation of the principle of "one country, two systems"
will become a reality, taking the first step in the country's
reunification.
</P>
<P>
"It is imperative for us to adhere to the basic principles of
peaceful reunification and 'one country, two systems' and
implement the eight-point proposal put forward by Jiang
Zemin," the meeting said.
</P>
<P>
Unremitting efforts must be made to oppose all splitting
activities and ideologies of "Taiwan independence", preventing the
Taiwan authorities from conducting internationally the splitting
activities of "two Chinas" and "one China, one Taiwan."
</P>
<P>
Efforts must also be made to facilitate direct links in mail,
trade and air and shipping services, personnel exchanges and
economic and cultural relations across the Taiwan Straits, and
earnestly protect the legitimate rights and interests of Taiwan
compatriots.
</P>
<P>
The meeting urged the Taiwan authorities to "return with
concrete actions to the principled stand of one China, by taking
into account the interests of the state, and respond to China's
proposal to hold negotiations as early as possible on such
political topics as ending the state of hostility across the
Taiwan Straits."
</P>
<P>
Chen Yunlin, director of both the Taiwan Working Office of the
CPC Central Committee and the Taiwan Office of the State Council,
presided over the meeting and made a work report. 
</P>
</TEXT>
