<HEADLINE> Five Soldiers Killed in Eastern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Five soldiers were killed today
when they repulsed an attack by Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam
(LTTE) rebels in Eastern Province of Sri Lanka, according to
military sources here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The sources said a group of LTTE rebels attacked an ambush
party of government forces while they were returning to the
Meegasgodella Camp.
</P>
<P>
The government troops retaliated and repulsed the attack
successfully. However, at least five soldiers were killed during
the fighting, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They added that LTTE casualties are not known.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a 14-year guerrilla war against the
government in the north and east of the country in a bid to
establish a separate Tamil state.  
</P>
