<HEADLINE> Thailand to Push for Farm Products Liberalization </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Thailand plans to push for
liberalization of processed agricultural products, according to a
Thai Commerce Ministry official.
</P>
<P>
Thailand would raise the issue at the senior officials' meeting
of the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC), scheduled to be
held shortly to discuss preparations for the annual ministerial
meeting later this year in Canada, Rachandra Pojanasuntorn, deputy
director general of the Business Economics Department, said on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Rachandra said it is time for APEC members to discuss farm
liberalization after the so-called quadripartite group, consisting
the United States, Canada, the European Union and Japan, succeeded
in pushing through its agenda to liberalize information technology
products.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has potential in food and agricultural processing as
well as hand-made products.
</P>
<P>
"We must strongly push for their liberalization under APEC," he
said.  
</P>
