<HEADLINE> Share Prices Fall on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices declined in less
active trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark Straits
Times Industrials Index fell by 5.63 points to close at 2,242.71
points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume dropped from the last few days to
196.74 million units, valued at 468.46 million Singapore dollars
(about 334.61 million US dollars). Declines led advances 205 to
135, while 253 other counters stayed steady.
</P>
<P>
Second Chance was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 41.97 million units. It was followed by
Lien Hoe TRS97 which had 10.03 million shares traded. CSH was next
with 8.42 million of its shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
Rashid Hussain topped the gainers' list as it rose by 60 cents
to 11.5 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 gained 50 cents to finish
at 17.5 Singapore dollars, while Shangri-La was 34 cents higher at
4.64 dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Easyknit was the biggest loser as it declined
by 2.1 dollars to 1.18 Hong Kong dollars. Local property developer
CityDevelopment warrant98 was next, falling by one dollar to end
at 10.9 Singapore dollars. The United Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign
lost 70 cents to close at 16.5 Singapore dollars.  
</P>
