<HEADLINE> 42 PKK Militants Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA,January 24 (Xinhua) -- Some forty militants of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in the past
five days of military operations by the Turkish security forces
in southeastern Turkey, local newspaper Daily News reported
today.
</P>
<P>
According to the Emergency Rule Region office, 27 PKK
militants were killed by the security forces in Wednesday and
Thursday fighting near the southeastern town of Bingol, and 15
PKK rebels were killed in other operations in the provinces of
Sirnak and Van.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the security forces also seized large amount of
weapons and ammunition.
</P>
<P>
There were no casualty reports of security forces during
these military operations.
</P>
<P>
In addition, several PKK members surrendered to the security
forces in the southeastern town of Semdinli, according to the
office.
</P>
<P>
More than 21,000 people have been killed in southeastern
Turkey since the PKK began a fighting for self-rule 12 years
ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
