<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Launches "Intelligent Cable" Producing Base in Jiangsu </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China has formed the first
manufacturing base for "intelligent cable," a special
multifunctional cable supporting computer networks, in Jiangsu
Province, to provide more advanced cable for the country's
information superhighway.
</P>
<P>
Known as "No.5 Cable," the intelligent cable developed by
Jiangsu-based Zhongtian Optical Cable Group has passed a technical
appraisal by experts from China's ministries of posts and
telecommunications, electronics industry and broadcast, film and
television, reported China Electronics News.
</P>
<P>
The intelligent cable can be used in "intelligent buildings,"
office buildings based on high-speed computer networks, and other
computer webs linked to the information superhighway subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Involving 40 million yuan, the intelligent cable project by
Zhongtian Group has an annual manufacturing capacity of 50,000 km
of cables. The equipment for the project was imported from
Austria, Switzerland and France.
</P>
<P>
China has launched "intelligent building" projects in 500 cities,
and will establish test centers for the intelligent cable products,
the paper said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
