<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0142 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sino-US Venture Is Top Supplier of Switching Machines in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Ten Chinese provinces and
cities are to give their telephone sectors a major boost by
creating millions of new phone lines.
</P>
<P>
They plan to buy switching machines that will provide 2.45
million lines from a Sino-Lucent Technologies joint venture in
Qingdao, Shandong Province. The aim is to largely improve the
transmission volume and speed of the country's telephone networks.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a ceremony to receive the ISO9001 quality
certificate from the International Quality System Certification
Agency, DNV, Michael Shen, president of Lucent Technologies
Qingdao Telecom Equipment Ltd., said that the venture, which was
founded in 1995, has sold more than two million lines of its
5ESS-2000 switch gears in China. The venture has extended its
market to 12 coastal provinces and municipalities.
</P>
<P>
Developed by Bell Laboratories in 1992, the 5ESS-2000 machine
is the most advanced switching system in the world with a large
transmission volume and high transmission speed.
</P>
<P>
According to a memorandum of understanding signed by Lucent
Technologies and China's State Planning Commission, Lucent
Technologies will transfer 5ESS-2000 technology to China.
</P>
<P>
The Qingdao-based joint venture currently has a single-shift
manufacturing capacity of 1.5 million lines of switching equipment
per year, with the proportion of domestic products in the
technical support system accounting for 78 per cent.
</P>
<P>
Shen said that the venture is the biggest manufacturing center
for program-controlled switch gears Lucent Technologies has ever
launched outside the US. Its output now accounts for eight
percent of the country's switching machine market.
</P>
<P>
Located in a hi-tech zone in Qingdao, the venture involves a
joint investment of 100 million US dollars from Lucent
Technologies and four Chinese partners. It is the largest joint
venture in the city. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
