<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Effective in Cracking Down Fake and Smuggled Cigarettes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China has tightened the
monopoly of tobacco production and circulation in the past year,
and achieved positive results in cracking down on fake and
smuggled cigarettes.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics compiled by the State Tobacco Monopoly
Administration (STMA), China investigated and handled 140,000
cases of illegal tobacco operations or malpractices in 1996,
tracking down and confiscating 2.79 billion smuggled cigarettes
and 3.95 billion fake or shoddy cigarettes.
</P>
<P>
In addition, STMA, together with relevant departments,
destroyed 383 fake and shoddy cigarette production bases,
confiscating 389 cigarette processing machines and
equipment.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
