<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympic Games Mascots Unveiled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The organizing committee of
the 2000 Sydney Olympic Games has chosen the anteater, the
platypus and the kookaburra bird as mascots of the Summer Olympic
Games.
</P>
<P>
The trio mascots are named "Millie", "Syd" and "Olly". They
will be featured on clothing and other souvenirs as well as in
marketing and promotional efforts for the 2000 Olympics.
</P>
<P>
The anteater, the platypus and the kookaburra are unique native
animals of Australia though they are less famous than kangaroo and
the koala bear.
</P>
<P>
The organizers said the three mascots represented the earth,
air and water. 
