<HEADLINE> Ugandan Rebels Join Zairean Army in Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The rebels of Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) of Uganda crossed the western border and
joined the Zairean army in its fighting against Tutsi rebels,
local media claimed today.
</P>
<P>
Over 300 ADF fighters have now established four bases inside
western Zaire, visiting Zairean businessmen told Ugandan
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
The businessmen who preferred to be anonymous for security
reason said Zairean Tutsi rebels have lost towns of Uvira and
Walikale in their battles launched by the combined forces of
Zairean army, ADF and an ethnic group named Wangelima supporting
the Zairean government.
</P>
<P>
They said Zairean Tutsi rebels in some places are now on the
run. A spokesman for Tutsi rebels said Kisaasi Ngandu, their
leader, was injured in an ambush. Earlier reports claimed Ngandu
was killed. 
</P>
