<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Recover Unauthorized Arms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangladeshi police will soon
begin a house-to-house search to recover unauthorized arms under a
special measure to improve the law and order situation in the
country, reliable sources said here today.
</P>
<P>
The operation will be carried out by several squads comprising
the Detective Branch and the Criminal Investigation Department of
the police.
</P>
<P>
A police survey showed that a large number of licensed arms
were used on a rental basis while illegal arms changed hands
frequently in Bangladeshi cities, where crime rates and terrorism
activities are on the rise.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
