<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's JVP To Contest Local Polls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Janatha Vimukthi
Peramuna (JVP), popularly known as the People's Liberation Front,
has announced Thursday that it will be contesting the forthcoming
local government elections, according to informed sources here
today.
</P>
<P>
The JVP is an anti-government Sinhalese political group in the
southern areas of the country where they had carried out
anti-government activities from 1971 to 1989.
</P>
<P>
Tilvin Silva, General Secretary of the JVP, announced Thursday
evening at a meeting that the party will contest the forthcoming
local polls at a national level, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The JVP which had a clear economic policy for the country was
opposed to the government's privatization program, the sources
added.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka will hold new local government elections in March
this year. The Election Commission announced Thursday that
nominations for local government elections will be held from
February 5 to 12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
