<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mystery Disease Kills 18 in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A mystery disease killed 18
people within 48 hours while 40 others are admitted to hospital
in Namwala, Southern province of Zambia, the local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
While confirming the outbreak of the disease, Namwala district
director of health Bernard Mulaso said, ''people here are dying
from this disease whose cause we do not know. People are dying at
a very fast rate because within a day or two someone complains,
one dies.''
</P>
<P>
Area board chairman John Malumbe said that most of the
patients died complaining of chest pains, a disease perhaps
which has something to do with dead rats.
</P>
<P>
Malumbe said, ''in the last two weeks, Namwala District
Hospital has registered 18 deaths resulting from similar
complaints and locals here think it is because of the dead rats
they find in bore-holes and wells where they draw drinking water."
</P>
<P>
"Even us medical personnel are not sure of the cause of the
disease,'' he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
