<HEADLINE> Philippines to Attend Singapore Monetary Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines has been invited
to take part in an international conference on derivatives of
exotic currencies to be held in Singapore in early March, the
Philippine News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Asia Business Forum Pte. Ltd., the two-day
conference will be attended by financial experts from Malaysia,
South Korea, Singapore, Thailand and the Philippines.
</P>
<P>
The Philippines will be represented by Caridad Valdehuesa,
treasurer of the Bureau of the Treasury, who will elaborate the
country's current monetary regulations and currency liberalization
policies.
</P>
<P>
Delegates to the conference are expected to consult with
financial experts, who will share detailed accounts of the latest
currency derivative products available in the market and the
recent developments in risk management, the report said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
