<HEADLINE> Cold Wave Expected to Continue in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- A cold wave sweeping Bangladesh
is likely to continue for five more days after taking 11 lives in
the last three days, according to an official weather bulletin
published here today.
</P>
<P>
It said that cold wind from distant north has been keeping the
mercury down for the last couple of days, and no marked change in
the weather is likely in the coming days.
</P>
<P>
Weather experts said chilly wind and rain made life difficult
in the far north districts of Tetulia and Panchagarh, where a deep
fog led to poor visibility and slow movement of the traffic.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that the poor and the destitutes are the worst
sufferers under the cold spell.
</P>
<P>
Thousands of warm clothes have been sent to these northern
districts but are yet to be distributed by the local governments,
official sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
