<HEADLINE> Hingis, Zvereva Win Australian Open Doubles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Switzerland's rising star
Martina Hingis paired with Natasha Zvereva of Belarus to capture
the women's doubles title of the Australian Open in Melbourne on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, playing with Zvereva for the first time, beat
Americans Lindsay Davenport and Lisa Raymond 6-2, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Hingis, who teamed with Helena Sukova of the Czech Republic to
win the Wimbledon doubles champion last year, will vie for the
Australian singles title against Mary Pierce of France on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Zvereva, the beaten doubles finalist with Davenport earlier
this month in the Sydney International, won 12 grand slam doubles
titles with American Gigi Fernandez from 1992 to 1996.
</P>
<P>
Zevreva and Fernandez had won the Australian doubles title
twice in 1993-94. 
</P>
