<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Sets Up Third National-level State-owned Oil Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China has set up its third
national-level state-owned petroleum company, following the China
National Petroleum Corporation (CNPC) and the China National
Offshore Oil Corporation (CNOOC).
</P>
<P>
A ceremony to mark the founding of the company, named China
National Star Petroleum Corporation, was held in Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the event, Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua said
that the establishment of the company shows that "China has taken
a significant step in the reform of the oil industry."
</P>
<P>
The company, with a registered capital of 3.1 billion yuan
(about 373 million US dollars), is formed by eight oil bureaus and
10 research institutes attached to the Ministry of Geology and
Mineral Resources.
</P>
<P>
Over the past four decades, the bureaus and institutes, which
boast a strong contingent of geologists, have discovered a number
of oil and gas fields in China.
</P>
<P>
Unlike the other two national-level state-owned oil companies,
the company will develop both onshore and offshore oil and gas
resources. Moreover, it will focus on the development of gas
resources, said Zhu Jiazhen, president of the company.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that his company will develop gas and oil resources in
East China Sea, in the north part of Jiangsu Province, the west
part of Sichuan Province, the Tarim Basin, the South China Sea,
the Tibet Autonomous Region and other areas.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome all overseas companies to cooperate with us in
developing oil and gas resources," he said, adding that the
company will also explore resources in other parts of the world.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the company plans to discover 350 to 450 million tons
of oil equivalent in proven and controlled reserves by the end of
century.
</P>
<P>
By 2000, the company's total output of gas and oil is expected
to reach 4.0 to 4.5 million tons of oil equivalent. It will also
develop downstream industries and diversify production so that its
total output value will reach 10 billion yuan (about 1.2 billion
US dollars) annually.
</P>
<P>
"The company strives to become a medium-sized international oil
company in 15 years," Zhu predicted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
