<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0172 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Output of Pharmaceutical Industry Up in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The output value of China's
pharmaceutical industry reached 120 billion yuan (14 billion US
dollars) in 1996, up 15 percent from 1995, said an official with
the State Pharmaceutical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
Zheng Xiaoyu, director of the bureau, said that his bureau has
improved the operation of the pharmaceutical market, curbed the
practice of trading medicines to accept kickbacks from sales, and
cracked down on production and sales of fake and shoddy medicines.
</P>
<P>
In some areas, drug stores and markets without licenses have
been closed, he said.
</P>
<P>
New laws and regulations on the production and the packaging of
medicine have been formulated. Pharmaceutical companies have
stepped up the reforms in their operations and a large group of
new enterprises have been set up, Zheng said.
</P>
<P>
The pharmaceutical industry implemented the strategy of
development through science and education. The assessment of key
projects of medical science and technology for the 1991-1995
period has promoted the development of the industry as a whole, he
said.
</P>
<P>
But problems such as too many small pharmaceutical factories
and the low production level of the industry still remain to be
solved, said Zheng.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the bureau will focus on the structural
adjustment of the pharmaceutical sector and the rectification of
the market order in the next few years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
