<HEADLINE> Air India to Suspend South Africa Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, January 24 (Xinhua) -- With continuous drop in
business, Air India, along with two other international airlines,
might be forced to stop its South Africa operations, the Hindustan
Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
In fact, the India's national carrier has already decided to
stop bookings from February 16 in view of slack business, the
newspaper quoted trade sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
The other two airlines that are having weak trade are the Gulf
Air and the Ethiopian Airlines. The two airlines have partly
suspended their South Africa operations.
</P>
<P>
Confirming the stoppage of bookings, however, an Air India
spokesperson said this did not mean operations from South Africa
would be withdrawn.
</P>
<P>
He said business was expected to pick-up during the middle of
the year and then during the December holidays.
</P>
<P>
The decision by Air India has come as a big blow to many South
Africans of Indian origin who have supported the airline since it
began operating a few years ago.
</P>
<P>
However, many passengers have also expressed frustration with
the airline's shoddy service both on flight and at ground.
</P>
</TEXT>
