<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, January 23 (Xinhua) -- The Stabilization Force (SFOR)
and the International Police Task Force (IPTF) have confiscated a
large amount of weapons belonging to the Croat police.
</P>
<P>
A SFOR spokesman said today that the weapons, including
anti-tank missiles, two missile launchers, mines and 85 grenades,
were found by a SFOR and IPTF joint patrol party in the secret
arsenal of a Croat police station in west Mostar.
</P>
<P>
The IPTF believe the weapons were not such to be used by
police, the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The SFOR have notified the Bosnian Croats, Serbs and Muslims
that they have to declare all their arms before February 15 and
undeclared arms found after the deadline will be confiscated and
destroyed. 
