<HEADLINE> Haikou Jinpan Industrial Zone in Shape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, January 24 (Xinhua) -- More than one billion yuan in
industrial output value was generated last year from 45
enterprises in the Jinpan Industrial Zone in Haikou, the capital
of Hainan Province.
</P>
<P>
The figure represents an increase of 160 percent over the
previous year, according to a survey, and the output value of
high-tech industrial enterprises in the zone last year accounted
for 73.5 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
Jinpan has developed into a new urban district with a
population of 6,000. It has four banks, one insurance company, two
schools, one post office and numerous shops, restaurants and
clinics.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the zone imported ten industrial projects with
actual investment of 181.5 million yuan. 
