<HEADLINE> Bangkok to Host Technology-Health Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, January 24 (Xinhua) -- Bangkok will host an
international conference on science and health early next month.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, claimed to be the first-ever in the country, will
discuss opportunities and challenges in the next century and
implications for the improvement of the quality of life in
Southeast Asia, according to Dr. Natth Bhamarapravati, chairman of
the Organizing Committee.
</P>
<P>
The conference, to be held on February 1-5, will focus on six
main fields including implications for health; nutrition and
development; control and prevention of infectious diseases
currently emerging or re-emerging; and reproductive health.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Natth said most developing countries, including Thailand,
had not placed enough emphasis on the development of science and
technology in the field of health.
</P>
<P>
He said that although Thailand has made strides in the fields
of reproductive health, nutrition and polio eradication, the
country needs to improve its use of scientific discovery to
control and eradicate other diseases and improve quality of life.
 
</P>
