<HEADLINE> Former Adversaries in Joint Naval Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Countries around the Black Sea and
former Western adversaries will hold a joint naval exercise near
the Crimean peninsula in August.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian Press Agency reported that the exercise,
code-named "Gentle Wind -- 97", will aim at coordinating navies
during future humanitarian operations.
</P>
<P>
The Ukrainian Navy Press Center said that besides the six Black
Sea area countries -- Ukraine, Romania, Bulgaria, Greece, Turkey
and Russia -- the exercise will also be participated in by the
United States, Britain, France, Germany and Italy.
</P>
<P>
Georgia and Albania would send observers to the exercise.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine will provide ten ships and some aircraft for the
exercise, and its Donuzlav naval base will be used, said Captain
Yuri Grokhov, leader of the preparation committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
