<HEADLINE> Singaporean Company to Build Beach Resort in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, January 24 (Xinhua) -- The Tech Built Construction Pte
Ltd of Singapore is planning to build a beach resort hotel at
Palongitan (also known as Nwagyi Nwange) Island in Kawthoung
region, the southern end of Myanmar bordering Thailand, official
paper The New Light of Myanmar today quoted director of the
company Drake Poh as disclosing.
</P>
<P>
In his meeting with Myanmar Minister for Hotels and Tourism
Kyaw Ba here on Thursday, Drake said his company intends to invest
40 million U.S. dollars for the world-class 250-room hotel
project, the report added.
</P>
<P>
To promote its tourism industry, Myanmar has opened some
islands including The Thahtay and Salon islands in Kawthoung to
foreign investors to build beach resorts, of which an Andaman Club
Resort Hotel at the Thahtay island, the first of its kind, was
built and opened in November 1995 by the Andaman Club Co Ltd of
Thailand.
</P>
<P>
A total of 113,169 tourists from Thailand visited Kawthoung and
Thahtay island beach resort in 14 months between November 1995 and
December 1996, according to official statistics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
