<HEADLINE> Russia to Use New Cosmodrome For Launch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia will use its new
"cosmodrome", which is located in the Far East Amur region, to
launch a military satellite after the middle of this year, the
Itar-Tass news agency reported here today.
</P>
<P>
This will be the first launch from the Svobodny cosmodrome
(derived from cosmos - the universe), the press officer of the
Russian Military Space Forces said.
</P>
<P>
The launch, which was originally scheduled for September, 1996,
with a United States remote-probe spacecraft as its commercial
payload, had to be postponed until the middle of this year due to
the U.S. experts' delayed preparations, the officer said.
</P>
<P>
The press officer said the launch would be attended by
representatives of companies from the United States, Sweden and
Canada, which were potential customers in future spacecraft
launches from the site. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0224 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Italy Records Slight Drop in AIDS Cases in 1996 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Italy had a slight drop in Aids
cases for the first time in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Epidemiologists from the Aids Center at the Superior Health
Institute noted in a report that up to December 31, 1996, a total
of 37,170 AIDS cases had been reported, 600 fewer new cases than
expected.
</P>
<P>
However, the head of the center, Giovanni Rezza, said it was
not yet clear whether this drop was due to delays in reporting new
cases or to the effects of new therapies used to combat the
disease.
</P>
<P>
According to Rezza, the region most hit was Lombardy, followed
by Lazio, Emilia-Romagna and Liquria -- all having a rate of more
than 12 cases for every 100,000 inhabitants.
</P>
<P>
The Institute also found that the average age at which a person
is diagnosed with Aids had risen over the past ten years, from 29
to 35 for males and from 24 to 33 for females.
</P>
<P>
Children under 12 years of age made up 1.6 percent of the
total. The institute also found that in the paediatric cases,
93.6 percent of the children had contracted the infection from
their mothers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0225 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Welcomes Czech-German Reconciliation Declaration </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Russia welcomes the joint
declaration of reconciliation signed between the Czech Republic
and Germany early this week, Russian Foreign Ministry spokesman
Gennady Tarasov said today.
</P>
<P>
Tarasov said that the declaration, which was signed by Czech
Prime Minister Vaclav Klaus and German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in
Prague Tuesday, would play an active role in helping build a new
Europe as well as promoting peaceful co-existence between the
Czech and German peoples.
</P>
<P>
However, Tarasov also expressed Russia's discontent over the
commitment Germany made in the declaration to support the Czech
Republic's efforts to obtain membership of the North Atlantic
Treaty Organization (NATO).
</P>
<P>
He said Russia is firmly opposed to the alliance's planned
eastward expansion, saying that no security would be ensured by
joining the organization. 
</P>
