<HEADLINE> China Attaches Importance to Luxembourg Ties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, January 24 (Xinhua) -- China attaches great
importance to the friendly cooperation with Luxembourg and greatly
appreciates Luxembourg's one-China policy, a senior Chinese
official said here today.
</P>
<P>
China's State Planning Commission Minister, Chen Jinhua, who is
visiting the Grand Duchy, said in an interview with Luxembourg's
Prime Minister, Jean-Claude Juncker, that China and Luxembourg had
great complementarity and a promising future in economic
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
He said the two countries should further strengthen their
economic ties, especially in fields like finance and metallurgy.
</P>
<P>
Juncker said the two countries, though having made great
achievements in their economic and trade cooperation, should
further tap potentials.
</P>
<P>
Chen and his entourage will leave for Switzerland Saturday to
attend the annual symposium of the World Economic Forum to be held
in Davos. 
</P>
