<HEADLINE> Beijing Police Arrest Prostitutes And Gamblers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, January 24 (Xinhua) -- In their latest crackdown on
pornographic materials and gambling activities, police in the
Chinese capital have arrested 12 people accused of acting as pimps
or of gambling.
</P>
<P>
Police also sent ten prostitutes and customers of brothels for
re-education through labor, and revoked licenses of ten night
clubs that were found to be providing pornographic or gambling
services, authorities announced on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"There are still lots of problems in Beijing's entertainment
spots in spite of the police crackdown on prostitution and
gambling," Zhang Liangji, director of the Beijing Municipal Bureau
of Public Security, pointed out.
</P>
<P>
More than 3,000 cultural and entertainment centers have
appeared recently in Beijing along with the economic growth and
improved standard of living.
</P>
<P>
And "Some businessmen disregard the laws and become involved in
illegal deals in pursuit of exorbitant profits," Zhang said,
noting that the police will continue their efforts to stop illegal
business practices and clean up the culture market.  
</P>
