<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dongxing Becomes Convenient Transit Point to Viet Nam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beihai, January 24 (Xinhua)-- Over 5,000 Chinese tourists go to
Viet Nam through the Chinese border city of Dongxing everyday.
</P>
<P>
They choose Dongxing as a transit point not only because it is
a booming trade city, but also because of the simplified and
convenient cross-border formalities it offers.
</P>
<P>
Due to the need to facilitate fast growing trade and tourist
links since the normalization of Sino-Vietnamese relations,
Dongxing has taken measures to shorten the time for handling
cross-border procedures. Now it can arrange a one-day tour
passport to Viet Nam within one hour. It also offers three-day and
one-week tour documents.
</P>
<P>
In the first nine months of 1996, the number of out-bound
Chinese tourists passing Dongxing increased by 88.4 percent as
compared with the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
In 1995, Dongxing ranked number one among the 18 Chinese border
cities in the number of out-bound tourist flows handled.
</P>
<P>
The improved road conditions, including the availability of
expressways and high-grade highways, also contribute to the
booming border tourism of Dongxing, which is conveniently located
600 kilometers away from the tourist city of Guilin, and 170
kilometers away from Beihai at the Beibu Gulf. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
