<HEADLINE> More Than 10 Drowned in Boat Mishap in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, January 23 (Xinhua) -- At least 13 people were
reportedly drowned this afternoon in a boat mishap in River Ravi
at Jaranwala, southwest of Lahore, provincial capital of Punjab.
</P>
<P>
According to a report by the Associated Press of Pakistan,
rescue workers have so far recovered the bodies of 13 people,
including seven women and two children. 30 other persons survived
the mishap by jumping out of the boat which has about 60 people on
board at the time of the accident.
</P>
<P>
The Police fear that the death toll might rise as search is on
for the missing passengers.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the survived boatman, Ahmed Ali, as saying
that the boat was caught in fast currents of the river and went
out of the control and it subsequently capsized.  
</P>
</TEXT>
