<HEADLINE> Russian Wins Men's Title at European Figure Skating </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Alexei Urmanov
of Russia took the title of the men's event after winning the
final free stating at the European Figure Skating Championship
here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Urmanov was only sixth in Wednesday's short program, but he
staged a dramatic comeback in the free skating competitions.
</P>
<P>
It was the first time since the Winter Olympics in Lillehammer
three years ago that Urmanov won a major title.
</P>
<P>
Philippe Candeloro of France finished second while defending
champion Viacheslav Zagorodniuk of Ukraine came third. 
