<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0245 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Swiss Independent Panel to Present Report on Nazi Gold </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, January 23, (Xinhua) -- An independent investigation
panel will present a report about its studies on the Swiss
National Bank's transactions of gold with Nazi Germany during
World War Two, Prof. J.-F. Bergier said today.
</P>
<P>
Bergier told the Swiss federal council (government) that he
expected the report would be ready before summer.
</P>
<P>
The Swiss government was satisfied with the progress of the
investigation which was said to take three to five years,
according to a press release by the government task force today.
</P>
<P>
The government will wait for "historically corroborated facts"
before deciding if it will take part in financing a fund for
Holocaust victims and their families.
</P>
<P>
Head of the task force Thomas Borer briefed the government on
his assessment of the situation and the work of the task force.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
