<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ukrainian Equals European Record in Short-Course Swimming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HELSINKI, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Denis Silantchev of Ukraine
equalled the 100-meter butterfly European record at a short-course
swimming meet at Espoo, Finland, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Silantchev clocked 52.51 to equal the eight-year old record set
by Michael Gross of Germany.
</P>
<P>
Silantchev also won the men's 200-meter butterfly with a
season's best time of 1:55.57 on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
World champion Jani Sievinen of Finland, won his speciality of
men's 200-meter individual medley in 1:58.52. It was his third
title in the two-day meet.
</P>
<P>
Mi Tong of China also took three titles in the women's
competitions and her teammates added two more golds.
</P>
<P>
The short-course World Cup will continues in Malmo, Sweden, on
Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
