<HEADLINE> France Salutes UN Nomination of Special Envoy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- France today saluted and
expressed its full support for the nomination by the United
Nations of Algerian Mohammed Sahnoun as the special representative
of the U.N. and the Organization of African Unity (OAU) to the
Great Lakes region of Africa.
</P>
<P>
Sahnoun, 65, worked for the U.N. in Somalia in 1992 and in
Congo in 1993. He clashed with the then U.N. Secretary-General
Boutros Boutros-Ghali over the U.N. policy in Somalia before
resigning from the post of U.N. envoy in the eastern African
state.
</P>
<P>
"We salute the designation of Mr. Sahnoun as special and
common representative of the U.N. and OAU for the region of Great
Lakes. The nomination of this prominent diplomat is a very
important step which we have been waiting with impatience," said
French Foreign Ministry spokesman Jacques Rummelhardt.
</P>
<P>
He said that Sahnoun can fully count on the support of France
for his mission.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the step will be followed by
the holding of an international conference on peace, security and
development of the Great Lakes region and international support
for the holding of elections in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
"What is important is the future of Zaire and the whole region.
We expect Mr. Sahnoun and the special envoy of the European Union
(EU) for the Great Lakes region of central Africa, Aldo Ajello, to
work with close liaison," said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
He also said that the common efforts to be made by the U.N.,
OAU and EU will "authorize reasonable hopes of peace for this
roughly tested region." 
</P>
</TEXT>
