<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unconditional Cooperation With Int'l Tribunal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, January 23 (Xinhua) -- U.N.
Under-Secretary-General for Legal Affairs Hans Correll has said
that it is the position of the United Nations that unconditional
cooperation with the International Tribunal is imperative.
</P>
<P>
He has also said that Republika Srpska should surrender Dr.
Radovan Karadzic and General Ratco Mladic as well as all other
accused within that entity to the International Tribunal to stand
trial.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks Wednesday in response to a letter from the
president of the Serb Repubic, which argued that Dr. Karadzic and
General Mladic should not be subject to the jurisdiction of the
International Tribunal.
</P>
<P>
Correl said that the tribunal, as the representative to the
international community as a whole, was a guarantee of an
independent, impartial and fair trial for all accused individuals.
</P>
<P>
"The Stature of the International Tribunal and the Rules of
Procedure and Evidence, by which it is bound, are an expression of
the highest standards of human rights and due process of law, and
a built-in guarantee for the rights of the accused," he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
