<DOCNO> XIE19970124.0259 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-01-23 20:54 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Warns Against U.S. Military Strike </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, January 23 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani said here today that Iran will powerfully respond to
any possible U.S. military measure and reveal to the world the
real power of Iran.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a gathering of Iranian press officials, Rafsanjani
said that the United States has harbored deep malice toward Iran
following the victory of the Islamic revolution in 1979.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani made it clear that regional security was indivisible
from Iran's security and that Iran plays a fundamental role in
safeguarding regional security.
</P>
<P>
Without doubt, he noted, lack of security in Iran means
insecurity in the whole region, and in such a case the U.S. will
not feel any rest.
</P>
<P>
It is unlikely that the U.S. would dare any aggression against
Iran, he concluded.
</P>
<P>
Then, Iranian Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati claimed that
the situation in the Persian Gulf is rather "tense" and "unsafe"
due to foreign military presence, especially the United States.
</P>
<P>
Velayati called the military presence of foreign powers
"unprecedented in the world" and serves as "obstacle to economic
development in this part of the world."
</P>
<P>
"Such a tense and endangering environment would weaken the
spirit of independence and initiative and instead prevail the
balance of fear, doubt and suspicion in the region," he noted.
</P>
<P>
Some Western media reports have said that Washington is working
out a special military program to strike 19 Iranian targets,
including some military training camps and nuclear reactors.
</P>
<P>
The keys to defuse the dangerous situation, the Iranian foreign
minister said, are regional cooperation, bilateral dialog and
trust-building measures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
